                   <strong> Scholarship Description:</strong>
                    </h2>
                    <p>Vidyadhan Scholarship Program 2018 invites applications from class 10 passed students from the state of Andhra Pradesh, Gujarat, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Telangana, Maharashtra and Kerala. 
                        The scholarship aims to provide an annual financial assistance of up to INR 6,000 for the students belonging to the economically weaker background.
                        The scholarship is being offered by Sarojini Damodaran Foundation</p>
                                    <hr>
                                      
                                   <h2> <strong>Eligibility for the Scholarship:</strong>
                                    </h2>
 <p>
 
To be eligible for this scholarship, an applicant must-
<ul>
<li>A student should be among the top 10% in class 10 & 12 & CET/JET ranks in his/her state.</li>
<li>Have secured admission to professional courses like Engineering, Medical, Dental, Po•	An applicant must be a class 10/SSLC passed out from the states of Andhra Pradesh, Gujarat, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Telangana, Maharashtra and Keralalytechnic, B.Sc (Agr), B.V.Sc etc. in a government or government-aided college.  </li>
<li>The annual family income of the applicant should be less than INR 2 Lakhs..</li></ul>
</p>
